{"title":"Wolf Tooth adds Larger, Lighter, Cheaper Aero Chainrings for SRAM","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-aero-chainring-for-sram-cranks/","date":1715361978000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-2-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"wolf tooth components aero chainring for sram cranks\" /></p>\n<p>If you’ve gone 1x for road or gravel, the new Wolf Tooth Aero Chainrings give you a sleek way to drop a little drag with SRAM cranksets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Already <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-aero-chainrings-shimano-grx/\">available for Shimano GRX</a>, these new versions fit SRAM’s 8-bolt direct mount cranks and Quarq Power Meter Spiders with 107 BCD. Depending on your setup, they’re offered in 46, 48, 50, and 52 tooth counts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of wolf tooth components aero chainring for sram cranks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-1.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All are machined with 7075-T6 aluminum at Wolf Tooth’s HQ (check out our <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/factory-tour-wolf-tooth-components-shows-us-around-we-spy-three-prototypes/\">factory tour here</a>) in Minnesota, USA. They’re optimized for SRAM Eagle, Flattop, and T-Type/Transmission chains, but also compatible with most 9/10/11-speed chains plus 12-speed chains from KMC, Connex, Wippermann and Campagnolo.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"507\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4-1536x507.jpg\" alt=\"chain management closeup on wolf tooth components aero chainring\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4-1536x507.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4-297x98.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4-120x40.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4-768x253.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-4-2048x676.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All sizes feature their DropStop narrow-wide tooth profile, but you can pair it with their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-lonewolf-aero-chainguide-corrals-your-1x-setup/\">Lone Wolf chain guides</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"wolf tooth components aero chainring options for sram cranks\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Wolf-Tooth-Components-aero-chainrings-for-sram-5.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 8-bolt aero chainrings start at $119.95 and weigh as little as 133g. The four-bolt 107BCD models for power meters are also $119.95 and weigh as little as 121g. If you’re keeping track, that’s about half the price and lots lighter than SRAM’s 1x aero chainring offerings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Available for pre-order now, shipping by June 14. Not concerned with aerodynamics? They still offer replacement 1x chainrings for 8-bolt direct mount cranks in 34, 36, 38, 40, 42, and 44 tooth sizes, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/collections/aero-chainrings\" target=\"_blank\">WolfToothComponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-aero-chainring-for-sram-cranks/\">Wolf Tooth adds Larger, Lighter, Cheaper Aero Chainrings for SRAM</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"94317e876c7ce3c332c15b181b6284803ee89dbc9922670d61fe058704df669a","category":"Cycling"}